            <div class="Header" style="text-align:center"><h1>Restoration</h1></div>
        <div class="Body">
            <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The goal of restoring a painting is to remove surface grime and discolored varnish layers, treat or reinforce support, replace “missing portions imitating the original by the sympathetic use of similar pigments or building up fragments of sculpted or moulded areas of an artwork.”<sup><a href="Bibliography.html#Work11">[11]</a></sup> Any restoration work done on a painting should be reversible, and retouching should always be limited to specific areas that need it.<sup><a href="Bibliography.html#Work11">[11]</a></sup></p>
